==English==

===Alternative spelings===
*[[ghole]]

===Etymology===
[[Farsi|Persian]] '''[[ghl]]''' &mdash; an imaginary sylvan demon, supposed to devour men and animals
: compare [[Arabic]] ''ghl'' and [[French]] ''[[goule]]''

===Noun===
'''ghoul'''  (''plural:'' '''[[ghouls]]''')
# ''(mythology, folklore)'' A [[spirit]] said to feed on [[corpse]]s.
# A [[graverobber]]; a person with an undue interest in death and corpses.

